Steward was born in the United Kingdom and moved to Townsville, Australia in 1983, and Brisbane in 1989.
Steward is most well known for his work in band Screamfeeder which formed in 1991, of which he is the singer, guitarist and principal songwriter.
He is also currently performing in Brisbane band We All Want To, who have released three critically acclaimed albums.
In 2006, Steward released his first solo studio album under Reverberation entitled How Does It End.
